        COLS="50" WRAP="virtual">>But I think enchanter pets can consume 
>up to 3 daggers per casting. 
>
>Of course their daggers only cost 1 
>sp each. 
>I'm not saying I wouldn't like to 
>see a vendor selling an unlimited 
>supply of chips(would make sense to 
>have one of these in Neriak). 
>
>But I was just pointing out that 
>there are chips out there for 
>the buying. 
>And newbies above level 2 frequently kill 
>skelies. Skelies bone chips sell for 
>1 sp and a few copper 
>verses bat wings, wasp wings, etc 
>which generally go for 8 cp 
>or so. 
>Also skelies can carry weapons worth a 
>couple gold now and then. They're 
>a good loot monster when you 
>don't have pups to kill. 
>Make bone chip runs. I had a 
>shaman that used snake skins for 
>one of her spells. Rather than 
>sit in Halas or Qeynos and 
>look for them(or kill snakes myself), 
>I just ran to Freeport and 
>bought about 15 stacks of 20. 
>
>By the time I made level 14 
>and had my new armor spell(which 
>outdated the one that used the 
>skins), I still had around 10 
>stacks of skins I needed to 
>dump. 
>If you got cash, hang around in 
>e commons, nro for a couple 
>hours and let it be known 
>you're buying bones for gold. 
>Get huge stacks of chips. Travel to 
>Feydwer(maybe visit a few dungeons while 
>your there), make a level 1 
>elf, raid the shops, and let 
>it be known to the newbies 
>that your necro is in the 
>market for chips. 
>Conserve chips. Don't burn a full stack 
>trying to get a pet that's 
>one level higher than the one 
>you have. 
>Hold contests. "(insert cool weapon here) for 
>whomever collects for me the most 
>bone chips in the next half 
>hour." Then buy the chips off 
>the losers too. 
>There's no reason a level 20 necro 
>needs to run around killing decaying 
>skelies for chips. 
>
>Hmmm... maybe all us necro's should hold 
>weekly contests on our servers for 
>bone chips.... Festival of the Dead? 
>We can show up with the 
>prizes and let everyone scramble to 
>bid bone chips on them... 
>I can see a new economic system 
>starting up here too.... 
>Allicia auctions "BBC for sale: starting bid 
>150 bone chips". 
> Allicia auctions "Needed, words for level 
>34 pet: willing to pay 300 
>BC!!!". 
> Madness, madness I say!!! 
